Hello,

As the poll question of my other tut passed.
Well, here is a little tutorial on making donator shops, pk shops, using points instead of coins.
[b]Here is the tutorial on how to add Donor Points:[/b] http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,522746.msg3802185.html#msg3802185


[size=14pt]Step 1:[/size] [size=12pt][u]Adding Shop.[/u][/size]

[b]1-[/b] Open [b]Shops.cfg[/b] and look which id is coming next.
you will see something like this:
<blockquote>//-----ShopID---ShopName---
shop = 1
shop = 2
shop = 3
....</blockquote>
So, if your last shop id is 18 you will go ahead and add a new line with the shop id 19. Like this:
[code]shop = 19	Donator_Store		2	2	1040	10[/code]
"[i]1040[/i]" = item id, "[i]10[/i]" = amount in shop. To add more items, add the item id's you want and add their amount like so.
[code]shop = 19	Donator_Store		2	2	1040	10      1042     10      1044      10[/code]


[b]2-[/b] Go into [b]ActionHandler.java[/b] and add a the NPC.
[code]			case 240:
				c.getShops().openShop(19);
			break;[/code]
"[i]case 1111[/i]" is the NPC which will handle the shop.
"[i]c.getShops().openShop(19);[/i]" means that it will open our shop id 19 from [b]Shops.cfg[/b].


[b]3-[/b] Put your NPC in-game.
Open [b]Spawn-Config.cfg[/b] and add a new line like this one:
[code]spawn = 240 	XXXX	YYYY	0	0	0	0	0	Description...[/code]
This will spawn the NPC 240 in your server. Edit your "XXXX" & "YYYY" by the position you want them to be.

Ok, now your shop is added and you have some items into it! :D
Right, so now let's go ahead and put these items prices..

[hr]

[size=14pt]Step 2:[/size] [size=12pt][u]Adding Price.[/u][/size]

So now, you want to be able to buy your items with your points..

[b]1-[/b] Open [b]ShopAssistant.java[/b] and search something like this:
[code]public void buyFromShopPrice[/code]
under this add:
[code]		if (c.myShopId == 19) {
			c.sendMessage(c.getItems().getItemName(removeId)+": currently costs " + getSpecialItemValue(removeId) + " Donor Points.");
			return;
		}
[/code]
This means when the player will click on the item in the shop, it will give him the price in Donor Points.


[b]2-[/b] Changing the item price.
In [b]ShopAssistant.java[/b] again, look something like this:
[code]public int getSpecialItemValue[/code]
and add this:
[code]
case 1040:
return 15;
[/code]
This means your item id "1040" will cost 15 Donor Points.
[u]NOTE[/u], each items you've added in your donator shop into [b]shops.cfg[/b], You have to declare them there also.


[b]3-[/b] in [b]ShopAssistant.java[/b] again, Search for:
[code]public void handleOtherShop[/code]
and right after this add:
[code]
			} else if (c.myShopId == 19) {
				if (c.donorPoints >= getSpecialItemValue(itemID)) {
					if (c.getItems().freeSlots() > 0){
						c.donorPoints -= getSpecialItemValue(itemID);
						c.getItems().addItem(itemID,1);
						c.getItems().resetItems(3823);
					}
				} else {
					c.sendMessage("You do not have enough Donor Points to buy this item.");			
				}
			}
		}
[/code]
this will make your items buyable with your points..

[b]4-[/b] in [b]ShopAssistant.java [/b] search for:
[code]int Slot = 0;[/code]

under this, you'll see something like this:
[code]			if (c.myShopId >= XX) {
				handleOtherShop(itemID);
				return false;
			}[/code]

right after this add:

[code]			if (c.myShopId == XX) {
				handleOtherShop(itemID);
				return false;
			}		[/code]
NOTE* Replace the XX by your shop Id.
This will declare your shop and will use the actual donor points.

That's it,
[u]if you have any errors just post them here and we'll see.[/u]

